children.brief: Implemented size:1536 bytes = (3 private copies) x (32 banks) x (2 words per bank) x (8 bytes per word) | Memory Usage:128 MLABs | Number of banks:32 | Bank width (word size):8 bytes | Bank depth:2 words | Number of replicates:1 | Number of private copies:3 | RAM Mode:Simple dual-port | Pump configuration:Single-pumped

details.Implemented size: 1536 bytes = (3 private copies) x (32 banks) x (2 words per bank) x (8 bytes per word)

Additional information.text: In each private copy:</br>  Variable 'bundle' occupies memory words [0-32] and has 1 array element split across 32 memory words.</br>  Memory words [33-63] are unused padding.
For each replicate, 3 private copies were created to enable simultaneous execution of 3 loop iterations defined at  (%L)
You can reduce the number of copies of this memory by limiting the concurrency of its loop.
